  "response": "Several types of events typically generate extensive news coverage on US evening news:\n\n1. Presidential elections and major political campaigns\n2. Major natural disasters (hurricanes, wildfires, earthquakes)\n3. Significant terrorist attacks or mass shootings\n4. High-profile criminal trials\n5. Major Supreme Court decisions\n6. Major sporting events (Super Bowl, World Series, Olympics)\n7. Presidential inaugurations\n8. State of the Union addresses\n9. Major economic events (stock market crashes, significant job reports)\n10. International conflicts or wars\n11. Space exploration milestones\n12. Presidential or high-profile political scandals\n13. High-profile celebrity events or deaths\n14. Major health emergencies (COVID-19 pandemic)\n15. Significant technological breakthroughs\n\nThese events tend to capture public attention and are considered newsworthy enough to receive extensive coverage across multiple news broadcasts.",
